[In neither situation was the serotype of meningococcus mentioned. In
recent WHO reports from 2006 outbreaks in Africa, however, except for
W135 found in Kenya, all outbreaks (Sudan, Uganda, Niger) have had
type A isolates found, as well the 2005 outbreak in Delhi. - Mod.LL]
